[> ML401 Flasher
--------------------------------------

This small tool programs binary images into the NOR flash
of the Xilinx ML401 development board.

It uses the DLC9 JTAG cable (Xilinx Platform Cable USB).

A special bitstream should be loaded into the FPGA. Its
purpose is to create a scan chain on the flash pins. The
behaviour is similar to that of the EXTEST instruction,
except that all unneeded signals have been removed to
significantly increase available bandwidth.

To load this bitstream, type "make load" in the "board"
directory. This will automatically build and load the
bitstream using iMPACT.

Then, the host-side tool can be used. It depends on
libusb 1.0. In the "host" directory, type "make" to
compile it. Then, run it with the raw binary image
you want to program as parameter.

Beware: the tool does not verify that the flash is
correctly programmed.


